f they do not agree with said laws. <p></br><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~shay01/morksiggy.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/usapiens1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sapiens1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/23/02 12:22:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The War of Northern Agression (aka Civil War)</span><hr size=1> But it was about slavery.<br><br>Because as you said it was &quot;do the states have the right to ignore laws passed by the Federal Government if they do not agree with said laws.&quot;<br><br>And which law was it that the southern states disagreed with?<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/umorkenlar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morkenlar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Councilman</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/23/02 12:55:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The War of Northern Agression (aka Civil War)</span><hr size=1> The proposed law/ammendment that all new states would be non slave states, Rob.<br><br>Remember - Lincoln didn't want to abolish slavery, he was just didn't want it in the new states - was basically his whole platform. <p></br><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~shay01/morksiggy.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ufesteringwounds.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fester